Here in this holy scripture is professed the One True Way of Pholtus of the Blinding Light, mighty god of Truth, Justice and Light that has dominion over the natural order of things. Never doubt of his powers for it is He that set the sun and the moon in the sky and maintains them in their rigid procession to show all creatures in this world the One True Way.

His is the only path that guarantees righteousness, the only path to a soul's salvation. Do not listen to the falsehoods of lesser gods, they are misleading and corrupt the soul. Only Pholtus can guide the soul of mortals toward enlightenment. Be upright and true in your devotion to Pholtus, spread his Will, reveal His blessed Light and the knowledge of the One True Way to the unbelievers. The world shall thus become a better place by the glorious light of Pholtus.

The One True Way of Pholtus is pure and cannot be questioned. Chaos, Darkness, Evil and Arcane magic must be destroyed and purged from this world at all cost.

Do not fall for the weaknesses of doubt and mercy, for the corrupt only thrive on such behaviors. You will forsake the temptations of luxury. You shall remain honest and faithful, valorous and just at all time. Carry a source of light with you at all time to remind yourself of the One True Way.

Bless be Pholtus of the Blinding Light, our beacon of Justice in this world of Darkness.

Value.value: The largest and most beautiful structure in town the Temple walls are festooned with statuary and glittering golden inlay. An intricate tower rises above the main entrance and prominently displays a holy symbol.Along the wall to your left is a network of scaffolding accompanied by a lone laborer making repairs to the iconic statues. Hundreds of flowers and bouquets lie in heaps on the ground below. Nearby, an old woman wrestles with a sack piled with bouquets of wildflowers obviously gathered from outside the city. As pedestrians move around her, she calls out... Flowers for the dead.
